The SEC rules obviously do not apply to you in Kenya.

56:16.340 --> 56:20.820
I don't know what rules do apply in Kenya though, so you should check.

56:20.820 --> 56:26.140
And then you probably have to be a little bit careful if you have US participants that

56:26.140 --> 56:28.500
are practically, you have an enforcement risk.

56:28.500 --> 56:32.860
Probably if you have a small project in Kenya, that would have been a security under US securities law,

56:32.860 --> 56:35.980
but under Kenya, it's a 50 ETH project.

56:35.980 --> 56:38.060
No, it's probably practically going to bother you.

56:38.060 --> 56:40.020
This is not legal advice.

56:40.020 --> 56:46.660
But if it becomes large and huge and successful, I don't know, you never know, the US regulatory

56:46.660 --> 56:49.460
authorities can be quite globally ambitious at times.

56:49.460 --> 56:56.420
So, you still need to be careful, my suggestion.

56:56.420 --> 57:00.660
And I think there are interesting things to explore that are not securities.

57:00.660 --> 57:02.580
So I am going to wrap up here.

57:02.580 --> 57:06.500
It's been about an hour, so I can take some questions.

57:06.500 --> 57:11.500
So let's take it again from the beginning.

57:11.500 --> 57:17.300
Step one, is it a security or not?

57:17.300 --> 57:22.980
If it is not, right, you can sell it to anyone.

57:22.980 --> 57:28.620
If it is, you either need to do an IPO, which practically speaking, you're not going to

57:28.620 --> 57:34.780
do, or you need to sell it only to Accredited Investors, or, you need to take advantage of

57:34.780 --> 57:42.500
the Reg A exemption for crowdfunding, which is also not totally none, not totally trivial.

57:42.500 --> 57:52.740
And so what that means in practice is because of these limitations imposed by the United

57:52.740 --> 58:05.780
States, even in this highly decentralized world, most things are funded by VCs.

